sedolisin : Sequence files representing the different subfamilies were extracted from the non-redundant GenBank database [26] using sedolisin, kumamolisin, and the human CLN2 sequences as queries to the web-based version of the BLAST program [27]: .
sedolisin : As is expected for a family of proteins, highly-conserved segments were found aligned to the crystal structure-identified core regions of the sedolisin and kumamolisin sequences.
sedolisin : Subsequently, the sequences were divided into two groups: those closer to sedolisin than kumamolisin and vise-a-versa.
the sedolisin : The alignment of these two groups was then manually set by the observed structural alignment of the sedolisin and kumamolisin proteins.
