Conclusion : Conclusion  CLN2 is very highly conserved and widely distributed among higher organisms and may play an important role in their life cycles.
Conclusion : Conclusion  CLN2 is very highly conserved and widely distributed among higher organisms and may play an important role in their life cycles.
Conclusions : Conclusions  Since the catalytic machinery of CLN2 matches closely that of sedolisin, kumamolisin, and other members of the family of serine-carboxyl peptidases, the enzymatic mechanism of all these enzymes is most likely the same.
